## Safety notes (both paths)

- **Never edit the theme directly on wordpress.com's dashboard / file editor.** Any server-side edit gets overwritten the next time we deploy, because both paths sync the entire theme directory. All edits go through git → PR → merge → deploy.
- **Compliance copy in `inc/compliance.php` is legally load-bearing** (AllayPay processor audit). Reverting accidental edits to that file is the single most important reason to enforce the no-direct-editing rule.
- **Activation state is stored in WP options**, not in theme files. Activating / deactivating the theme via the admin UI does not touch the repo and does not conflict with deploys.
- **Uploaded media (`wp-content/uploads/`) and installed plugins (`wp-content/plugins/`) are NOT deployed** by either path — they're server-side state, managed through WP admin or WP-CLI.
